Package: skmle
Title: Sieve Kernel Maximum Likelihood Estimation for Survival Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Dayu",
           family = "Sun",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "dayusun@iu.edu")
Description: Estimation and inference for transformed hazards models
    with sparsely and intermittently observed longitudinal covariates.
    Combines kernel-weighted log-likelihood and B-spline sieve maximum
    likelihood estimation in a unified framework, implementing the
    Sieve Maximum Kernel-weighted Log-likelihood Estimator (SMKLE) of
    Sun, Sun, Zhao and Cao (2025) <doi:10.1080/01621459.2025.2476781>.
    Specialized kernel estimating-equation estimators are provided for
    the proportional hazards and additive hazards cases, along with
    simulation and cross-validation utilities. The core numerical
    routines use 'Rcpp', 'RcppArmadillo' and the 'nloptr' C API for
    performance.
URL: https://www.sundayu.me/skmle/, https://github.com/dayusun/skmle
